    <div class="space-y-8">
      <div class="bg-white p-8 border-[3px] border-yellow-500">
        <h4 class="text-2xl font-black mb-4 text-yellow-600">Problem: "DNS Propagation Takes Forever"</h4>
        <p class="text-lg mb-4">
          <strong>Symptom:</strong> You updated DNS records, platform says "waiting for DNS," hours pass with no change.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg mb-4">
          <strong>Cause:</strong> DNS propagation takes 1-48 hours worldwide. Some ISPs cache DNS for 24-72 hours.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg mb-4">
          <strong>Solution:</strong> Wait 48 hours. Most domains propagate within 2-24 hours. Check with <code>whois.com/whois/yourdomain.com</code> to see if nameservers updated. If updated, wait 24-48 hours for global propagation.
        </p>
        <div class="bg-yellow-50 p-4 border-l-4 border-yellow-500">
          <p class="font-bold">üí° There's no way to speed up DNS propagation. It's internet-wide process that takes time. Be patient. Don't make changes during propagation or you restart the clock.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white p-8 border-[3px] border-orange-500">
        <h4 class="text-2xl font-black mb-4 text-orange-600">Problem: "www Works But Root Domain Doesn't" (or vice versa)</h4>
        <p class="text-lg mb-4">
          <strong>Symptom:</strong> yourdomain.com works but www.yourdomain.com doesn't (or opposite).
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg mb-4">
          <strong>Cause:</strong> Missing CNAME record for www (or missing A record for root).
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg mb-4">
          <strong>Solution:</strong> Add BOTH records provided by platform:
          <ul class="space-y-1 text-lg mt-2">
            <li>‚Ä¢ <strong>A Record:</strong> Points yourdomain.com to platform</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ <strong>CNAME Record:</strong> Points www.yourdomain.com to yourdomain.com (or to platform)</li>
          </ul>
        </p>
        <div class="bg-orange-50 p-4 border-l-4 border-orange-500">
          <p class="font-bold">üí° Most platforms provide both A and CNAME records. Add both. This ensures both yourdomain.com AND www.yourdomain.com work. Platform will specify exact records.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white p-8 border-[3px] border-red-500">
        <h4 class="text-2xl font-black mb-4 text-red-600">Problem: "Domain Already Exists Elsewhere"</h4>
        <p class="text-lg mb-4">
          <strong>Symptom:</strong> Platform won't let you add domain because it "exists elsewhere."
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg mb-4">
          <strong>Cause:</strong> Domain is connected to another platform/hosting service.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg mb-4">
          <strong>Solution:</strong> 
          <ol class="space-y-1 text-lg mt-2">
            <li>1. Go to OLD platform/hosting and disconnect domain</li>
            <li>2. Wait 1-2 hours for DNS to clear</li>
            <li>3. Add domain to NEW platform</li>
            <li>4. Update DNS records to point to new platform</li>
            <li>5. Wait 24-48 hours for propagation</li>
          </ol>
        </p>
        <div class="bg-red-50 p-4 border-l-4 border-red-500">
          <p class="font-bold">üí° Always disconnect from OLD platform before connecting to NEW. Having domain connected to two places simultaneously = conflicts, broken sites, headaches.</p>
        </div>
